  "source_notes": "Sy Scholfield quotes Bob Hammel, \"The Bill Cook Story: Ready, Fire, Aim!\" (Indiana University Press, 2008), p. 28: \"The Great Depression was tightening its chokehold on America when Cook was born in Mattoon, Illinois, on Tuesday, January 27, 1931, the first and only child of George and Cleo Cook. He arrived on what his mother remembered as an unusually warm day for January. She also remembered the sound of an Illinois Central Railroad train whistle blowing somewhere close at the very moment of her son's birth, 6:10 pm.\" \\n",
